Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: If you check the KMDLabs git there is a pos64staker repo

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: that repo has several commands to split your coins to many addresses and UTXOs.

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: Its a balance game... how much coin in each utxo, how many utcos per address compared to the rest of the stakers

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: All dictates your performance

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: The idea is... there are 64 SEGIDs, 0-63

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: Every address is tied to a single SEGID

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: the staker checks the next SEGID in order for a valid block solution, then moves to the next until someone has a valid utxo that meets age and a solution, then it stakes a block.

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: So, idea is, get a good amount of coin, and if you have enough, divide it among the SEGIDs into several UTXOs per SEGID

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: the repo explains how

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: if you dont have a good amount... its likely better to make a larger UTXO on a single address

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: you can evaluate the last staked SEGIDs totals per SEGID in the last X blocks by passing the daemon CLI the getlastsegidstakes X

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: So, the last ~24 hours would be...

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: komodo-cli -ac_name=LABS getlastsegidstakes 1440
